
Pre-Monsoon Conditions:
Before the monsoons, the water column in the Arabian Sea typically exhibits weaker stratification.
Surface temperatures may be warmer, and salinity may be more uniform because there is not as much freshwater coming in yet.

Expected Post-Monsoon Conditions:
The heavy rain brings in a lot of freshwater into our area of interest
Expect the surface salinity to decrease and temperature to decrease because the cloudy weather blocking the sun as well as the winds associated with Monsoons.



